WEBVTT

00:08:59.720 --> 00:09:02.536
and he says that he could tell
from the look on my face

00:09:02.560 --> 00:09:04.976
that something devastating
had just happened to me,

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:06.336
and I immediately told him.

00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:08.256
I mean, I would have told the concierge

00:09:08.280 --> 00:09:10.976
because that was the authority
person in the room, right?

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:12.856
As Scott Rosenberg has said, who else?

00:09:12.880 --> 00:09:16.656
There wasn't a fantasy
attorney general of Hollywood

00:09:16.680 --> 00:09:18.336
to whom I could report this.

00:09:18.360 --> 00:09:19.576
I did tell my agent;

00:09:19.600 --> 00:09:22.136
I told Gary Fleder who was
directing "Kiss the Girls,"

00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:23.976
the picture I was making at the time,

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:25.216
and everyone else on set.

00:09:25.240 --> 00:09:29.256
And I've run into scores of people
since this article came out on October 5

00:09:29.280 --> 00:09:31.976
who said, "Oh yeah, we were
sitting at that Kentucky game